# FSTEC agent — metacognition & Kaizen

When any error appears — test failure, build break, unexpected runtime — **stop guessing**.

Full skill: [.agents/skills/fstec-karpathy-guidelines/SKILL.md](../skills/fstec-karpathy-guidelines/SKILL.md) § Metacognition.

## Trigger

- `npm run typecheck`, `lint`, or `build` exits non-zero.
- Same failure twice after a fix.
- Cannot explain why in one sentence.

## Method: 5 Whys

Stop at a controllable root cause (code, config, missing env, plan gap).

## Gemba in FSTEC

- Reproduce: `npm run dev`, `curl` admin API and `/api/public/{token}`, inspect Postgres via `npm run db:studio`.
- Smallest fix at the true failure point.
- Re-run failing check; then full build.

## Kaizen note (PR / phase plan)

Symptom → root cause → fix → regression guard.

## Critic gate on bugfix PRs

- [ ] Root cause documented
- [ ] Failing command re-run green
- [ ] Kaizen note for non-trivial bugs
